## 5. Hybrid Search Design

### 5.1 Why Hybrid (Not Just Vector)

| Query type | Vector search | BM25 keyword | Winner |
|-----------|--------------|-------------|--------|
| "home network setup" | ✅ strong | ✅ strong | tie |
| "Configured Omada router" | ✅ good | ✅ exact | BM25 |
| "the machine running the gateway" | ✅ semantic | ❌ misses paraphrase | Vector |
| "a828e60" (git SHA) | ❌ meaningless | ✅ exact token | BM25 |
| `memorySearch.query.hybrid` (code symbol) | ❌ weak | ✅ exact | BM25 |
| "error when startup fails" | ✅ semantic | ⚠️ partial | Vector |

Hybrid search captures both signals. Use it as the default.

### 5.2 Merge Algorithm

```
Step 1: Fetch candidate pools
        Vector pool: top (maxResults × candidateMultiplier) by cosine similarity
        BM25 pool:   top (maxResults × candidateMultiplier) by FTS5 BM25 rank

Step 2: Normalize BM25 rank → score
        textScore = 1 / (1 + max(0, bm25Rank))   // 0..1 range

Step 3: Union candidates by chunk ID
        finalScore = vectorWeight × vectorScore + textWeight × textScore
        (normalize weights so vectorWeight + textWeight = 1.0)
        Recommended defaults: vectorWeight=0.7, textWeight=0.3

Step 4: Sort by finalScore descending

Step 5: (Optional) Temporal decay
        decayedScore = finalScore × e^(-λ × ageInDays)
        where λ = ln(2) / halfLifeDays (default halfLifeDays=30)
        Exception: evergreen files (MEMORY.md, non-dated memory/*.md) are never decayed

Step 6: (Optional) MMR re-ranking for diversity
        Iteratively pick results that maximize:
          λ_mmr × relevance − (1−λ_mmr) × max_similarity_to_already_selected
        Similarity measured via Jaccard on tokenized content
        Default λ_mmr = 0.7 (balanced; raise toward 1.0 for pure relevance)

Step 7: Return top maxResults
```

### 5.3 When to Enable Each Post-Processing Stage

| Stage | When to enable |
|-------|---------------|
| **Temporal decay** | Agent has months of daily notes; stale entries outrank recent ones |
| **MMR diversity** | Searches return near-duplicate snippets from similar daily notes |
| **Both** | Long-running agents with large daily note histories (recommended) |

### 5.4 Fallback Chain

Always degrade gracefully:

```
QMD sidecar (BM25 + vector + rerank)
    → on failure: built-in SQLite hybrid (FTS5 + vector)
        → if sqlite-vec unavailable: SQLite FTS5 + JS cosine similarity
            → if embeddings fail: BM25-only (still useful for exact tokens)
```

Never hard-fail on a memory search. Return an empty result set and log a warning.

