## 7. Memory Operations API Design

Every memory system needs at minimum these three operations:

### `memory_store(text, importance?, category?)`
- Generate embedding
- Check near-duplicates (threshold ≥ 0.95) before writing
- Store with auto-assigned UUID, timestamp, category
- Return `{action: "created" | "duplicate", id}`

### `memory_recall(query, limit?)`
- Embed the query
- Run hybrid search (vector + BM25)
- Apply temporal decay + MMR if configured
- Return ranked list with scores, categories, source references

### `memory_forget(memoryId? | query?)`
- By ID: delete directly (GDPR-compliant, O(1))
- By query: find candidates, require explicit confirmation if ambiguous (> 1 result, score < 0.9)
- Validate UUID format before any SQL operation to prevent injection

