## 8. Embedding Provider Strategy

The system supports five embedding providers with a priority-based auto-selection:

```
Auto-selection order (when provider is not explicitly set):
1. local (node-llama-cpp)  ← if modelPath is configured and file exists
2. openai                  ← if OPENAI_API_KEY is set
3. gemini                  ← if GEMINI_API_KEY is set
4. voyage                  ← if VOYAGE_API_KEY is set
5. mistral                 ← if MISTRAL_API_KEY is set
6. (disabled)              ← no key available
```

**Configuring a fallback:** Always set a fallback provider so transient API failures don't break memory entirely.

```json5
memorySearch: {
  provider: "openai",
  model: "text-embedding-3-small",
  fallback: "local"
}
```

**Batch embedding for large corpora:** Enable batch mode when indexing > 10,000 chunks. OpenAI batch API offers ~50% cost reduction and is asynchronous — fire and poll.

**Embedding cache:** Cache chunk embeddings in SQLite by `(chunkText hash + model + endpoint)`. On reindex, skip re-embedding unchanged chunks. This is critical for frequent session transcript indexing.

**Model dimension pinning:** Always store the model name and vector dimensions together. If the model changes, invalidate and rebuild the entire index — never mix embeddings from different models in the same table.

