## 9. Memory Compaction & Session Lifecycle

### 9.1 Pre-Compaction Flush

When a session approaches the context window limit, trigger a silent agentic turn to flush important information to disk before compaction discards it:

```json5
compaction: {
  memoryFlush: {
    enabled: true,
    softThresholdTokens: 4000,      // flush when this many tokens remain
    systemPrompt: "Session nearing compaction. Store durable memories now.",
    prompt: "Write any lasting notes to memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md; reply with NO_REPLY if nothing to store."
  }
}
```

This prevents important context from being silently lost during context window management.

### 9.2 Index Freshness Strategy

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| Memory file written (debounce 1.5s) | Mark index dirty, schedule async sync |
| Session start | Run sync if dirty |
| Search request | Run sync if dirty, then search |
| Interval timer (default 5m) | Run sync regardless |
| Model/endpoint fingerprint change | Full reindex |

Never block the agent on index sync. Run sync in the background and return slightly stale results if needed.

