## 10. Implementation Checklist for New Projects

Use this checklist when building a memory layer from scratch:

### Foundation
- [ ] Define your two-tier storage layout (canonical Markdown + derived index)
- [ ] Choose embedding provider and pin model name + dimensions in config
- [ ] Implement the five-gate capture filter (length, content smell, injection screen, trigger match)
- [ ] Store only user-role messages, never model output

### Storage
- [ ] Assign UUID v4 to each memory entry; never reuse
- [ ] Store `createdAt` timestamp in Unix ms for temporal decay
- [ ] Assign a `category` to every entry using a domain-specific taxonomy
- [ ] Implement near-duplicate detection (threshold ≥ 0.95) before write
- [ ] Add an embedding cache to avoid re-embedding unchanged content

### Retrieval
- [ ] Implement both FTS5 (BM25) and vector search
- [ ] Use weighted hybrid merge (default: 70% vector, 30% BM25)
- [ ] Add temporal decay for date-stamped memories (halfLife=30 days)
- [ ] Add MMR re-ranking if duplicate snippets are common
- [ ] Provide a graceful fallback chain (QMD → SQLite hybrid → FTS-only → empty)

### Security
- [ ] Screen all inputs for prompt-injection patterns before capture
- [ ] HTML-escape all stored text before injection into prompts
- [ ] Wrap injected memories in an "untrusted historical data" container
- [ ] Validate UUID format before any SQL DELETE operation
- [ ] Never surface memories in group/public channels by default (scope: DM-only)

### Operations
- [ ] Implement `memory_store`, `memory_recall`, `memory_forget` as explicit tools
- [ ] Implement pre-compaction flush to persist memories before context window truncation
- [ ] Make the index fully rebuildable from canonical Markdown at any time
- [ ] Log memory operations (store, recall, forget) with counts and reasons
- [ ] Allow users to delete memories by ID for GDPR compliance

